[
  {
    "startTime": 0.56,
    "endTime": 4.54,
    "text": "Are there any words that you're pronouncing\nwrongly in English?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 4.54,
    "endTime": 9.04,
    "text": "Let's find out."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 12.36,
    "endTime": 17.8,
    "text": "We're going to look at ten words that are\ntricky, see how some English learners say"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 17.81,
    "endTime": 20.948999999999998,
    "text": "them and see how Jay and I say them."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 20.949,
    "endTime": 23.400000000000002,
    "text": "So in British and American English."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 23.4,
    "endTime": 24.4,
    "text": "Ready?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 24.4,
    "endTime": 25.769,
    "text": "First word…"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 25.769,
    "endTime": 30.169999999999998,
    "text": "Comfortables - ah, no 's'."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 30.17,
    "endTime": 31.26,
    "text": "Comfortable."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 31.74,
    "endTime": 33.26,
    "text": "Comfortable."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 33.72,
    "endTime": 35.64,
    "text": "Comfortable."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 36.28,
    "endTime": 37.480000000000004,
    "text": "No, no, no."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 37.58,
    "endTime": 38.98,
    "text": "It's comfortable."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 38.99,
    "endTime": 40.09,
    "text": "Comfortable."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 40.09,
    "endTime": 42.300000000000004,
    "text": "3 syllables."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 42.3,
    "endTime": 48.239999999999995,
    "text": "We write it like it has 4 - comf-or-ta-ble,\nbut the 'or' disappears."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 48.32,
    "endTime": 51.34,
    "text": "Comfortable\nComfortable."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 51.76,
    "endTime": 55.04,
    "text": "That's the thing about English pronunciation."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 55.05,
    "endTime": 57.279999999999994,
    "text": "We often don't say what we write."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 57.28,
    "endTime": 58.28,
    "text": "OK."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 58.28,
    "endTime": 59.93,
    "text": "Next one."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 59.93,
    "endTime": 61.64,
    "text": "Months, months, months."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 62.08,
    "endTime": 65.74,
    "text": "Months\nMonths."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 66.04,
    "endTime": 67.86,
    "text": "Not bad."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 67.87,
    "endTime": 74.78,
    "text": "It's hard to pronounce this word because\nit's got the 'th' sound quickly followed"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 74.78,
    "endTime": 75.95,
    "text": "by 's'."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 75.95,
    "endTime": 80.32900000000001,
    "text": "You have to pull your tongue back very fast."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 80.329,
    "endTime": 82.08999999999999,
    "text": "Months."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 82.09,
    "endTime": 83.85000000000001,
    "text": "Months."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 83.85,
    "endTime": 85.689,
    "text": "Be careful not to say month-es."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 85.689,
    "endTime": 89.17899999999999,
    "text": "It's just one syllable."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 89.179,
    "endTime": 90.74000000000001,
    "text": "Months."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 90.74,
    "endTime": 92.6,
    "text": "Now here's a secret."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 92.6,
    "endTime": 98.53899999999999,
    "text": "If you say muns or munts, we'll understand."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 98.539,
    "endTime": 102.28,
    "text": "We say that too when we're speaking fast."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 102.28,
    "endTime": 104.04,
    "text": "Muns."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 104.04,
    "endTime": 105.799,
    "text": "Munts."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 105.8,
    "endTime": 109.14,
    "text": "OK, next one."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 109.14,
    "endTime": 111.52,
    "text": "Receep."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 111.53,
    "endTime": 113.39,
    "text": "Receep."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 113.39,
    "endTime": 115.249,
    "text": "Nope."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 115.249,
    "endTime": 117.109,
    "text": "Recipe."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 117.109,
    "endTime": 118.979,
    "text": "Nearly."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 118.979,
    "endTime": 124.899,
    "text": "It has three syllables but the stress is on\nthe first syllable."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 124.9,
    "endTime": 128.16,
    "text": "Recipe\nMmmm."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 131.7,
    "endTime": 134.95999999999998,
    "text": "This soup is delicious."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 134.97,
    "endTime": 138.12,
    "text": "It was my mother's recipe."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 138.12,
    "endTime": 140.34,
    "text": "The next word looks similar."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 140.44,
    "endTime": 142.72,
    "text": "Recept."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 142.72,
    "endTime": 144.74,
    "text": "Receipt."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 144.75,
    "endTime": 146.48,
    "text": "Recept."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 146.48,
    "endTime": 148.22,
    "text": "No."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 148.22,
    "endTime": 150.659,
    "text": "We don't pronounce the 'p'."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 150.66,
    "endTime": 152.56,
    "text": "It's silent."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 152.56,
    "endTime": 155.9,
    "text": "Receipt\nReceipt"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 155.9,
    "endTime": 161.68,
    "text": "A receipt is a document that shows you've\npaid for something."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 161.68,
    "endTime": 164.42000000000002,
    "text": "Let's hear it in a sentence."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 169.22,
    "endTime": 170.31,
    "text": "Yes?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 170.31,
    "endTime": 173.98,
    "text": "I'd like to return this sweater."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 173.98,
    "endTime": 175.11999999999998,
    "text": "Do you have the receipt?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 175.12,
    "endTime": 176.17000000000002,
    "text": "No, I'm sorry."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 176.17,
    "endTime": 177.57899999999998,
    "text": "I lost it."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 177.579,
    "endTime": 179.329,
    "text": "Did you pay by credit card?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 179.329,
    "endTime": 181.70000000000002,
    "text": "No, I paid cash."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 181.7,
    "endTime": 182.7,
    "text": "Then I'm sorry."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 182.7,
    "endTime": 184.069,
    "text": "I can't help you."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 184.069,
    "endTime": 186.0,
    "text": "But I just bought it this morning."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 186.3,
    "endTime": 187.48000000000002,
    "text": "Next word."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 188.0,
    "endTime": 190.02,
    "text": "Literature."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 192.12,
    "endTime": 194.96,
    "text": "Literature."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 196.22,
    "endTime": 198.7,
    "text": "Literature."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 198.92,
    "endTime": 200.33999999999997,
    "text": "It's hard."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 200.35,
    "endTime": 202.87,
    "text": "How many syllables does it have?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 202.87,
    "endTime": 205.859,
    "text": "Jay and I say it differently."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 205.86,
    "endTime": 208.28,
    "text": "Literature."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 208.34,
    "endTime": 211.02,
    "text": "Literature."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 211.02,
    "endTime": 213.87900000000002,
    "text": "Did you hear the difference?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 213.879,
    "endTime": 220.81,
    "text": "In British English it just has three syllables\nand in American it has four."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 220.81,
    "endTime": 222.92000000000002,
    "text": "Lit-e-ra-ture."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 222.94,
    "endTime": 225.6,
    "text": "Lite-ra-ture."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 225.98,
    "endTime": 227.67999999999998,
    "text": "Literature."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 228.06,
    "endTime": 229.98,
    "text": "Literature."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 230.76,
    "endTime": 235.28,
    "text": "There's a great way to practise long words\nlike this."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 235.29,
    "endTime": 237.51,
    "text": "It's called backchaining."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 237.51,
    "endTime": 243.0,
    "text": "You start at the back of the word and work\nforward."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 243.1,
    "endTime": 246.56,
    "text": "ture-rature-literature."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 246.56,
    "endTime": 247.8,
    "text": "Try it."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 247.9,
    "endTime": 252.26000000000002,
    "text": "ture-rature-literature."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 252.26,
    "endTime": 253.32,
    "text": "Great."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 253.38,
    "endTime": 254.82,
    "text": "Next one."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 254.829,
    "endTime": 257.47,
    "text": "Let's have something easier."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 257.47,
    "endTime": 259.34000000000003,
    "text": "Busy."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 259.34,
    "endTime": 261.19899999999996,
    "text": "Busy."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 261.199,
    "endTime": 266.44,
    "text": "It's nearly right but notice the vowel sound."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 266.44,
    "endTime": 272.259,
    "text": "It's not ooo - and it's not u like in\nbus."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 272.259,
    "endTime": 276.61,
    "text": "It's /I/ like in bit."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 276.61,
    "endTime": 278.96000000000004,
    "text": "Can we talk?"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 278.96,
    "endTime": 281.84,
    "text": "I'm a bit busy."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 281.86,
    "endTime": 283.04,
    "text": "Busy."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 283.42,
    "endTime": 284.6,
    "text": "Busy."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 285.98,
    "endTime": 289.20000000000005,
    "text": "OK, next one."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 289.26,
    "endTime": 292.82,
    "text": "Debt."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 292.82,
    "endTime": 295.12,
    "text": "Debt."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 295.12,
    "endTime": 297.78000000000003,
    "text": "No."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 297.84,
    "endTime": 300.94,
    "text": "Debt."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 300.94,
    "endTime": 303.21999999999997,
    "text": "Pretty close!"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 303.4,
    "endTime": 306.9,
    "text": "Debt. Debt."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 306.9,
    "endTime": 310.53999999999996,
    "text": "A debt is money that you owe someone."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 310.55,
    "endTime": 313.68,
    "text": "You borrowed some money and now you're in\ndebt."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 313.68,
    "endTime": 317.38,
    "text": "But the letter b is silent."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 317.38,
    "endTime": 319.4,
    "text": "Listen."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 319.4,
    "endTime": 321.40999999999997,
    "text": "Debt."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 321.41,
    "endTime": 323.43,
    "text": "Debt."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 323.43,
    "endTime": 327.66,
    "text": "Another word like that is doubt – when you're\nnot sure if something is true."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 327.66,
    "endTime": 328.72,
    "text": "Yes."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 328.72,
    "endTime": 330.72,
    "text": "That has a silent 'b' too."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 330.72,
    "endTime": 334.68,
    "text": "I doubt if you can say the next word."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 334.68,
    "endTime": 335.84000000000003,
    "text": "Let's see."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 335.84,
    "endTime": 336.84,
    "text": "Hierarchy."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 336.84,
    "endTime": 339.17999999999995,
    "text": "Hierarchy."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 339.18,
    "endTime": 342.039,
    "text": "Hierarchy."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 342.04,
    "endTime": 346.76000000000005,
    "text": "No, that's not right."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 346.76,
    "endTime": 349.26,
    "text": "Hierarchy."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 349.32,
    "endTime": 352.12,
    "text": "Hierarchy."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 352.12,
    "endTime": 358.24,
    "text": "This word means a system where people are\norganized into different levels of importance."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 358.24,
    "endTime": 362.36,
    "text": "So like in a company with the boss at the\ntop."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 362.4,
    "endTime": 364.46,
    "text": "Hierarchy."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 364.47,
    "endTime": 371.97900000000004,
    "text": "Hi-er-ar-chy – it's four syllables but\nsometimes we run the first two together so"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 371.979,
    "endTime": 374.419,
    "text": "it's almost three."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 374.419,
    "endTime": 375.419,
    "text": "Hier-ar-chy."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 375.419,
    "endTime": 377.229,
    "text": "Let's back chain it."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 377.229,
    "endTime": 378.59999999999997,
    "text": "Say it with me."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 378.64,
    "endTime": 383.34,
    "text": "chy – archy – hierarchy."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 383.34,
    "endTime": 385.599,
    "text": "Great, next one."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 385.6,
    "endTime": 387.64000000000004,
    "text": "This one's very common."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 387.7,
    "endTime": 389.18,
    "text": "Aren't."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 389.32,
    "endTime": 390.86,
    "text": "Aren't."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 390.87,
    "endTime": 392.24,
    "text": "Aren't."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 392.24,
    "endTime": 396.37,
    "text": "No, all wrong."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 396.37,
    "endTime": 401.509,
    "text": "When you contract are and not, you have to\nmake them one syllable."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 401.509,
    "endTime": 405.289,
    "text": "But Jay and I say this word differently."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 405.289,
    "endTime": 406.59,
    "text": "Listen."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 406.59,
    "endTime": 407.88899999999995,
    "text": "Aren't."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 407.889,
    "endTime": 409.199,
    "text": "Aren't."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 409.2,
    "endTime": 413.56,
    "text": "My r is much softer and Jay's is stronger."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 413.66,
    "endTime": 414.84000000000003,
    "text": "Aren't."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 414.84,
    "endTime": 416.84,
    "text": "Aren't."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 416.88,
    "endTime": 419.6,
    "text": "Say it the American way!"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 419.6,
    "endTime": 425.77000000000004,
    "text": "It doesn't matter which way you say it,\nbut make sure it has just one syllable."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 425.77,
    "endTime": 428.74,
    "text": "And sometimes we don't pronounce the 't'."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 428.74,
    "endTime": 429.75,
    "text": "Yeah."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 429.75,
    "endTime": 435.82,
    "text": "When we're speaking casually we both put a\nstop on the t, so it ends abruptly."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 435.82,
    "endTime": 436.56,
    "text": "Aren'."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 436.7,
    "endTime": 439.34,
    "text": "Aren' - We aren' finished yet."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 439.349,
    "endTime": 440.75,
    "text": "That's right."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 440.75,
    "endTime": 441.75,
    "text": "We aren'."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 441.75,
    "endTime": 444.74,
    "text": "Here's the next word\nCrisps."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 444.92,
    "endTime": 446.68,
    "text": "Crisps."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 446.68,
    "endTime": 448.43,
    "text": "Crisps."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 448.43,
    "endTime": 450.19,
    "text": "Crisps."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 450.19,
    "endTime": 451.95,
    "text": "Crisps."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 451.95,
    "endTime": 453.979,
    "text": "These are crisps."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 453.979,
    "endTime": 459.09,
    "text": "The tricky thing here is the 'sps' at the\nend – sps."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 459.09,
    "endTime": 461.38899999999995,
    "text": "Try it."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 461.389,
    "endTime": 463.98,
    "text": "sps. sps."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 464.08,
    "endTime": 469.02,
    "text": "Crisps\nCrisps"
  },
  {
    "startTime": 469.03,
    "endTime": 471.67999999999995,
    "text": "But we don't call these crisps in America."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 471.68,
    "endTime": 474.169,
    "text": "We call them potato chips."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 474.169,
    "endTime": 476.039,
    "text": "Say chips."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 476.039,
    "endTime": 478.12899999999996,
    "text": "No chips are different."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 478.129,
    "endTime": 479.819,
    "text": "We have fish and chips."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 479.819,
    "endTime": 481.68,
    "text": "They're French fries."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 481.68,
    "endTime": 484.0,
    "text": "OK, last word."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 484.0,
    "endTime": 486.58,
    "text": "This one's very tricky."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 486.58,
    "endTime": 488.00899999999996,
    "text": "Thoroughly."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 488.009,
    "endTime": 489.439,
    "text": "Thoroughly."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 489.44,
    "endTime": 492.78,
    "text": "Thoroughly."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 492.78,
    "endTime": 494.4,
    "text": "Thoroughly."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 494.4,
    "endTime": 498.0,
    "text": "No, I don't know."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 498.26,
    "endTime": 500.46,
    "text": "Thoroughly."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 500.66,
    "endTime": 503.72,
    "text": "Je sais pa."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 503.729,
    "endTime": 506.349,
    "text": "It's very hard."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 506.349,
    "endTime": 514.68,
    "text": "It's got a th sound and then an ^ vowel\nand then an r and an l sound."
  },
  {
    "startTime": 514.68,
    "endTime": 516.66,
    "text": "Thoroughly."
  },
